# Documentation

## Technical and User Manual

### Deployment
To deploy the application, follow these steps:
1. Clone the repository: `git clone https://github.com/amolina38/HealthInfo-AMES`
2. Navigate to the project directory: `cd to C:...HealthInfo-AMES`
3. Install dependencies: `npm install`
4. Build the application: `npm run build`
5. Start the server: `npm start`
6. Access the application via the provided URL, most likely localhost:3000

### User Instructions
To fully utilize the application and explore all features, follow these steps:
1. Open the application in your web browser, either using localhost or the depolyed version of our site through Vercel; https://ames-medication.vercel.app/
2. Sign up for an account by entering a valid email and a password of at least 6 characters.
3. Log in using your credentials.
4. Explore the various functionalities provided:
   - Submit New Entry: Fill in the fields above the "Submit New Entry" button. "Select Medication" and "Date" are required, "Notes" is not. Click the "Submit New Entry" button to see your entry populate.
   - Download Medication History: Click the "Download Medication History" button at the top left of the page to automatically download a JSON file of your existing medication history.
   - Delete Entry: Click the red trash icon to the left of a medication entry. When prompted with the confirmation pop-up asking "Are you sure you want to delete this entry?", click "Ok."
   - Sign Out: Click the "Sign Out button at the top right of the user page.

### Special Instructions for Grading
1. Navigate to the following URL: https://ames-medication.vercel.app/
2. Follow "User Instructions" found on this page.
